South Sydney Rabbitohs beat Canterbury Bulldogs 18-17 at ANZ Stadium on Friday night . 
  NRL head of football Todd Greenberg has vowed to issue Canterbury fans who threw bottles at match officials with life-time bans . 
  Referees and officials were struck with projectiles after a late penalty was awarded to South Sydney . 
  Sideline interchange official Darren Alchin was taken to hospital with a broken shoulder blade . 
  Canterbury fans threw water bottles and abuse at referee Gerard Sutton after the game . 
  Two people have been formally identified for allegedly throwing bottles . 
  Canterbury chief executive Raelene Castle has called for a life ban on fans involved in the incident . 
 